vstore.framework.context.types.network

Class VNetwork

  • java.lang.Object
    • vstore.framework.context.types.VContextType<VNetwork>
      • vstore.framework.context.types.network.VNetwork
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class VNetwork
extends VContextType<VNetwork>
    This class represents an instance of the Network context data. Contains information if WiFi is connected in this context (and what the SSID is), if mobile data is connected and if the type is 2G, 3G, 3.5G or 4G.

      • matches

        public boolean matches(VNetwork other)
        Matches the given network context against this network context. Matching WiFi SSIDs are considered a match, and matching mobile connection types are considered a match. But both at the same time is not checked. WiFi has higher priority than mobile. That means, if WiFi is connected and the same SSID is given, mobile is ignored.
        Specified by:
        matches in class VContextType<VNetwork>
        Parameters:
        other - The context to match against.
        Returns:
        True, if both contexts match. False, if not
